s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"how to write meta descriptions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"how to write meta descriptions for seo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"meta description generator\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"meta descriptions wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=37991\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:541:\"<p>Do you want to know how to write meta descriptions for SEO that’ll increase your organic search traffic, CTR (Click-Through-Rate), and rankings on Google? In this post, we’ll show you how to write meta descriptions for SEO, and to easily add them in WordPress. We’ll also cover what a meta description is and why you need it.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-for-seo/\">How to Write Meta Descriptions for SEO (Boost CTR & Rankings)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Kato Nkhoma\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31791:\"<p>Do you want to know how to write meta descriptions for SEO that’ll increase your organic search traffic, CTR (Click-Through-Rate), and rankings on Google?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Research by <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/recommends/ahrefs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Ahrefs</a> has shown that 74.98% of the top 10 ranking web pages have a meta description, which means it’s important to optimize yours for SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to easily write meta descriptions for SEO and add them in WordPress. We’ll also cover what a meta description is and why you need it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s a quick overview of what we’ll cover in this post. Simply click on these quick links to jump straight to different sections:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-a-meta-description-in-wordpress\">What Is a Meta Description in WordPress?</a></li><li><a href=\"#why-do-you-need-a-meta-description\">Why Do You Need a Meta Description?</a></li><li><a href=\"#how-to-write-meta-descriptions-for-seo\">How to Write Meta Descriptions for SEO?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-1-include-your-focus-keyword\">1. Include Your Focus Keyword</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-2-describe-your-pages-content\">2. Describe Your Page’s Content</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-3-include-a-call-to-action-to-increase-ctr\">3. Include a Call to Action to Increase CTR</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-4-be-unique-and-interesting\">4. Be Unique and Interesting</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#easily-add-your-meta-description-in-wordpress\">Easily Add Your Meta Descriptions in WordPress</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-use-the-ai-title-description-generator-to-effortlessly-create-meta-descriptions-with-1-click\">How to Automatically Add Meta Descriptions Using the AI Title/Description Generator (1-Click)</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-adding-your-meta-description\">How to Manually Add Your Meta Description</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-easily-double-check-that-youve-added-your-focus-keyword\">Easily Double-Check That You&#8217;ve Added Your Focus Keyword</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-analyzing-your-seo\">Analyzing Your SEO</a></li></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Alright, let’s get started by first explaining what a meta description in WordPress is.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-a-meta-description-in-wordpress\">What Is a Meta Description in WordPress?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A meta description in WordPress is an HTML element or attribute that gives a brief summary of what your web page is about.&nbsp;It gives searchers a sneak peek of your article on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/what-are-serps/\" title=\"What Are SERPs (And Why Are they Important to SEO)?\">search engine results pages</a> (SERPs), hopefully encouraging them to click on your search listing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example of a meta description on Google for the search query: “best keto recipes”:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"173\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-meta-description-on-google.png\" alt=\"Example of a meta description in Google\'s search results\" class=\"wp-image-33479\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-meta-description-on-google.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-meta-description-on-google-300x71.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/example-of-meta-description-on-google-600x142.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Google and other search engines often show the meta description in their search results. So by writing good, interesting and actionable meta descriptions, you can get more people to click through to your website and increase sales for your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-do-you-need-a-meta-description\">Why Do You Need a Meta Description?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Meta descriptions won’t directly help you rank, but compelling and actionable meta descriptions will convince more people to click on those links. More clicks mean more traffic, and it can also lead to higher rankings in search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, meta descriptions let Google know what your page is about. Even though Google doesn’t always use your meta description and sometimes adds its own based on your content, you should write them in case it does. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Writing good meta descriptions is especially important for your homepage, product and category pages since they help in establishing your brand.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"how-to-write-meta-descriptions-for-seo\">How to Write Meta Descriptions for SEO?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to writing meta descriptions for SEO, you should do the following:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Include Your Focus Keyword&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Describe Your Page’s Content&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Include a Call to Action </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Make Them Unique and Interesting</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>We understand that this can feel like a lot&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;but depending on the niche you’re active in and the purpose of your site, you should at least try to implement as many of the above as possible to maximize your search traffic, clicks, and rankings. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s dig in a bit deeper&#8230;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-1-include-your-focus-keyword\">1. Include Your Focus Keyword</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Every meta description should include the focus keyword or keyphrase that you want to rank for.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Always start by <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/best-seo-keyword-analysis-tool/\" title=\"8 Best SEO Keyword Analysis Tools You Need to Know in 2023\">performing keyword research</a> to find the best keywords for your content that have search volume and will match the search intent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding your focus keyword is also important because Google highlights search terms by bolding them when they match the user’s search terms. This helps users to notice them more easily.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, here you can see how Google has highlighted the search terms from the search query: “best SEO plugin for WordPress”:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"702\" height=\"213\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-example.png\" alt=\"Example of how to write meta descriptions and including the keyword.\" class=\"wp-image-172152\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-example.png 702w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-example-300x91.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-example-600x182.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-example-190x58.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/how-to-write-meta-descriptions-example-297x90.png 297w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 702px) 100vw, 702px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, it only takes a second to scan this meta description to see that it answers the search query, resulting in more clicks and higher rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-2-describe-your-pages-content\">2. Describe Your Page’s Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A good meta description should describe your page’s content. The recommended character limit is 155-160 characters, so you need to summarize your most important content in about 2 sentences.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO will help you get the right length. It shows how many characters you&#8217;ve used and warns if you exceed the max recommended characters for your meta description. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"173\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/max-recommended-characters-meta-description-in-asioseo.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-38156\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/max-recommended-characters-meta-description-in-asioseo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/max-recommended-characters-meta-description-in-asioseo-300x71.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/max-recommended-characters-meta-description-in-asioseo-600x142.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/max-recommended-characters-meta-description-in-asioseo-190x45.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/max-recommended-characters-meta-description-in-asioseo-380x90.png 380w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As easy as 1-2-3!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-3-include-a-call-to-action-to-increase-ctr\">3. Include a Call to Action to Increase CTR</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A call to action can prompt searchers not only to click on your link but also to do something once they arrive on your site. For example, <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-business-voip-and-internet-phone-systems/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">call a phone number</a>, sign up for a free trial, or take a special action.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s an example of MonsterInsights meta description, which lets people know that they can <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-set-up-google-analytics-on-a-wordpress-site/\" title=\"How to Set Up Google Analytics on a WordPress Site (Easy Way)\">set up Google Analytics for WordPress</a> with just a few clicks:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"147\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/call-to-action-meta-description-1.png\" alt=\"Call to action meta description for the best analytics plugin for WordPress MonsterInsights\" class=\"wp-image-38158\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/call-to-action-meta-description-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/call-to-action-meta-description-1-300x60.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/call-to-action-meta-description-1-600x121.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/call-to-action-meta-description-1-190x38.png 190w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/call-to-action-meta-description-1-447x90.png 447w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, the stats of 12 million downloads will also work as proof that other website owners are using the plugin and encourage searchers to download it as well. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-4-be-unique-and-interesting\">4. Be Unique and Interesting</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Many large sites auto-populate their meta descriptions, so the first thing you should do is to make sure they’re unique and interesting.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ask yourself this question: Would the meta description spike your interest to want to know more and click on the link? Put yourself in your customer’s shoes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Does this sound overwhelming?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>No need to worry because AIOSEO helps you easily write meta descriptions for SEO and add them to your site in a heartbeat, which we’ll show you next.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"easily-add-your-meta-description-in-wordpress\">Easily Add Your Meta Descriptions in WordPress</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the easiest ways to add meta descriptions in WordPress is to use a powerful SEO plugin like <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" title=\"Pricing\">All In One SEO</a> (AIOSEO).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"730\" height=\"447\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/all-in-one-seo-homepage.png\" alt=\"The best WordPress SEO plugin, All in One SEO\" class=\"wp-image-26967\" srcset