"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30307:\"<p>Are you thinking about downloading an AIOSEO Pro nulled plugin?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO Pro nulled plugins are pirated copies of the popular All in One SEO (AIOSEO) WordPress plugin. Nulled plugins pose serious security risks, from installing backdoors to hijacking your site for criminal intent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll explain why you need to avoid AIOSEO Pro nulled if you want to keep your blog and business website safe from hackers.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Try AIOSEO Pro Risk-Free</a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:32px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group aioseo-table-of-contents has-theme-info-background-color has-background\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>In This Article</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-table-of-contents\"><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-what-are-aioseo-pro-nulled-plugins\">What are AIOSEO Pro Nulled Plugins?</a><ul><li><a href=\"#aioseo-vulnerability-of-small-businesses\">Vulnerability of Small Businesses</a></li></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-security-threats-posed-by-aioseo-pro-nulled-plugins\">Security Threats Posed by AIOSEO Pro nulled Plugins</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-get-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-for-free\">How to Get AIOSEO for Free</a></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-all-in-one-seo-aioseo-pro-features\">AIOSEO Pro Features</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-how-to-get-a-aioseo-pro-license-key-free-aioseo-pro-latest-version\">How to Get a Pro License Key Free</a><ul></ul></li><li><a href=\"#aioseo-summing-it-up\">Summary: Don&#8217;t Install AIOSEO Pro Nulled</a><ul></ul></li></ul></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-what-are-aioseo-pro-nulled-plugins\">What are AIOSEO Pro Nulled Plugins?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO Pro nulled plugins are unauthorized, pirated copies of All in One SEO (AIOSEO) premium WordPress plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These nulled plugins (also called &#8220;cracked plugins&#8221;) are given away for free (or at a discount) on various websites.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>No websites offering AIOSEO Pro nulled plugins are affiliated with AIOSEO even though they use AIOSEO&#8217;s logo and features list.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Because these nulled plugins are unauthorized, site owners that install them are ineligible to receive support from All in One SEO (AIOSEO).</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>While genuine versions of AIOSEO have a license checking feature, in AIOSEO Pro nulled plugins this feature is disabled. AIOSEO Pro nulled plugins may be advertised as having a &#8220;free license key&#8221; or &#8220;activated key.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-aioseo-theme-notice-box\" role=\"alert\">\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/all-in-one-seo-pack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\"><strong>Get the Genuine AIOSEO Plugin for Free</strong></a><strong> </strong></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-why-is-aioseo-pro-nulled-dangerous\">Why is AIOSEO Pro Nulled Dangerous?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The security firm WordFence <a href=\"https://www.wordfence.com/blog/2021/01/the-wordfence-2020-wordpress-threat-report/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">found</a> that nulled plugins &#8220;typically contain backdoor functionality&#8221; and because of that, they&#8217;re &#8220;the most widespread threat&#8221; to WordPress websites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nulled plugins, including AIOSEO Pro nulled, are often used to inject malware. Security firms have published numerous reports on cyberattacks caused by nulled plugins. These include</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Installing backdoors so hackers can control your site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Installing skimmers to steal credit card information.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Injecting links, including to illegal websites.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hijacking sites to mine cryptocurrency.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>According to a <a href=\"https://www.wordfence.com/blog/2021/01/the-wordfence-2020-wordpress-threat-report/#malware-from-nulled-plugins-most-widespread-threat\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">recent report</a>, &#8220;malware distributed via nulled, pirated, or counterfeit plugins and themes&#8221; is &#8220;one of the largest threats facing the WordPress ecosystem.&#8221;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-vulnerability-of-small-businesses\">Vulnerability of Small Businesses</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Approximately <a href=\"https://www.verizon.com/business/resources/reports/2019/2019-data-breach-investigations-report.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">43%</a> of U.S. cyberattacks target small businesses. And <a href=\"https://cdn.advocacy.sba.gov/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/05122043/Small-Business-FAQ-2020.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">80%</a> of small businesses have no IT staff.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using AIOSEO Pro nulled, or any nulled plugin, exposes your business to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Revenue loss</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reputational loss</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Destruction of your SEO.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/aioseo-pro-nulled-1024x683.jpeg\" alt=\"aioseo pro nulled\" class=\"wp-image-166309\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/aioseo-pro-nulled-1024x683.jpeg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/aioseo-pro-nulled-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/aioseo-pro-nulled-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/aioseo-pro-nulled-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/aioseo-pro-nulled-2048x1365.jpeg 2048w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/aioseo-pro-nulled-600x400.jpeg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/aioseo-pro-nulled-90x60.jpeg 90w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/aioseo-pro-nulled-135x90.jpeg 135w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-security-threats-posed-by-aioseo-pro-nulled-plugins\">Security Threats Posed by AIOSEO Pro nulled Plugins</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are a few of the known security risks posed by nulled plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-injection-of-malware\">Injection of Malware</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Hackers <a href=\"https://www.wordfence.com/blog/2021/07/nulled-wordpress-plugins/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">often use nulled plugins</a> as vehicles for malware. Like the Trojan Horse of ancient Greece, the trick starts with convincing users they&#8217;re getting a great deal.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Beware: It can be difficult, costly, (or even impossible) to recover your site from a serious malware infection.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-installing-secret-backdoors\">Installing Secret Backdoors</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The malware&#8217;s often used to install secret backdoors. These allow bad actors to take over your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Backdoors can also be used to gain access to your email, computer, and/or web server.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, we know of a case where a site owner installed a nulled plugin, only to see his site hijacked to mine cryptocurrency.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hackers have also developed <a href=\"https://blog.sucuri.net/2021/12/php-re-infectors-the-malware-that-keeps-on-giving.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">zombified backdoors</a> that spring back to life after supposedly being removed.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-selling-access-to-your-site\">Selling Access to Your Site</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Sometime the hacker will add his own password protection to the backdoor so he can sell access to your website on the <a href=\"https://www.zdnet.com/article/a-cybercrime-store-is-selling-access-to-more-than-43000-hacked-servers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">black market</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These online cybercrime shops are thriving. There are even cybercrime stores selling hacked access to <a href=\"https://krebsonsecurity.com/2022/01/crime-shop-sells-hacked-logins-to-other-crime-shops/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\"><em>other</em></a> cybercrime stores.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-using-your-email-for-spam-or-phishing-attacks\">Using Your Email for Spam or Phishing Attacks</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Malware that compromises your mail server can give hackers access to your domain-based email.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That means they can send out email messages in your name and spread malware hacks to your customers and prospects.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"645\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/phishing-illustration-1024x645.jpeg\" alt=\"phishing illustration\" class=\"wp-image-166312\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/phishing-illustration-1024x645.jpeg 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/phishing-illustration-300x189.jpeg 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/phishing-illustration-768x484.jpeg 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/phishing-illustration-1536x968.jpeg 1536w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/phishing-illustration-2048x1290.jpeg 2048w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/phishing-illustration-600x378.jpeg 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/phishing-illustration-95x60.jpeg 95w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/phishing-illustration-143x90.jpeg 143w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-data-theft\">Data Theft</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Malware infections from nulled plugins can be used to steal customer records, intellectual property, and financial records.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This can lead to reputational and revenue loss for the targeted business. And it can leave your business exposed to liability risks.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-installing-card-skimmers\">Installing Card Skimmers</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Nulled plugins are known vectors for online skimmers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just like the skimmers at gas pumps, online skimmers steal credit card information in order to raid bank accounts</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-black-hat-seo-and-bad-links\">Black Hat SEO and Bad Links</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In this scenario the hacker injects links into your site. These links are designed to boost the SEO of various <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/search/docs/essentials/spam-policies\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" title=\"\">link schemes</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, the links may point to</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Illegal drug sites or porn sites</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sites that will download malware onto your users&#8217; websites.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Google penalizes sites that participate in link schemes. This means your website can be de-indexed (removed entirely from search results) and lose its search engine rankings you fought hard to obtain.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, Google&#8217;s Chrome browser may display a security warning when searchers access your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"440\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/google-security-warning-1-1024x440.png\" alt=\"google security warning\" class=\"wp-image-166314\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/google-security-warning-1-1024x440.png 1024w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/google-security-warning-1-300x129.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/google-security-warning-1-768x330.png 768w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/google-security-warning-1-600x258.png 600w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/google-security-warning-1-140x60.png 140w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/google-security-warning-1-210x90.png 210w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/google-security-warning-1.png 1307w\" sizes=\"100vw\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><em>Above: Example of a Google Chrome security warning. This particular one is for a page on a well-known cybersecurity company website. (We notified them of the issue.</em>)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"aioseo-adding-malicious-content-to-your-site\">Adding Malicious Content to Your Site</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Because they have access to your site, hackers can add malicious content to your site to spread infections further.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Indeed, hacks from nulled plugins are often designed to be hidden from WordPress administrators, so you may not even see that you&#8217;ve been hacked.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-lack-of-professional-support-and-documentation\">Lack of Professional Support </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you use a nulled version of All in One SEO (AIOSEO), you don&#8217;t get access to our professional support team.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Staffed with experienced engineers, our support team provides an array of services from assistance with SEO settings to answering and resolving advanced technical needs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Likewise, we publish and maintain clear documentation for our users. Plugin fees enable us to provide all of these services.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"aioseo-unethical-use-undermines-small-businesses\">Unethical Use Undermines Small Businesses</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We all like a good shortcut, but using a nulled plugin undermines the work being done at All in One SEO (AIOSEO).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;re a small team whose work includes:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Research and development of new software features.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Experimentation with SEO tactics and marketing strategies.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Growing our professional team of experienced engineers and growth marketers to